login page elements:
    Email/Phone Number/Username’ Textbox
    ‘Password’ Textbox
    Login Button

Test Scenarios Login Page:

1.Verify that cursor is focused on “Username” text box on the login page
2.Verify that User is able to Login with Valid Credentials
3.Verify that User is not able to Login with invalid Username and invalid Password
4.Verify that User is not able to Login with Valid Username and invalid Password
5.Verify that User is not able to Login with invalid Username and Valid Password
6.Verify that User is not able to Login with blank Username or Password
7.Verify that the password is in encrypted form when entered
8.Verify that spaces should not be allowed before any password characters attempted
9.Verify that clicking on browser back button after successful login should not take User to log out mode
10.Verify that clicking on browser back button after successful logout should not take User to logged in mode
11.Verify that the password is in encrypted form when entered
12.Verify the password can be copy-pasted
13.Verify that User should be able to login with the new password after changing the password
14.Verify that User should not be able to login with the old password after changing the password
15.Verify that spaces should not be allowed before any password characters attempted
16.Verify that the ways to retrieve the password if the User forgets the password
17.Verify that “Remember password” checkbox is unselected by default (depends on business logic, it may be selected or unselected)
18.Verify that “Keep me logged in” checkbox is unselected by default (depends on business logic, it may be selected or unselected)
19.Verify that the timeout of the login session (Session Timeout)
20.Verify that the logout link is redirected to login/home page
21.Verify that User is redirected to appropriate page after successful login
22.Verify that User is redirected to Forgot password page when clicking on Forgot Password link
23.Verify that User is redirected to Create an account page when clicking on Sign up / Create an account link
24.Verify that validation message is displayed in case when User leaves Username or Password as blank
25.Verify that validation message is displayed in case of exceeding the character limit of the Username and Password fields
26.Verify that validation message is displayed in case of entering special character in the Username and password fields
27.Verify whether the login form is revealing any security information by viewing page source
